reviewText: Was a great portrayal of a honorable man and President who was taken way too soon and had such a shocking affect on a child in fifth grade and can recount every moment that was mentioned in this DVD set being somewhat short but to the point ! Part of the reason I went into the Navy was because of his Ask not what your Country can do for you, but what you can do for your Country!
I was in middle school during the Kennedy presidency. That was a very innocent time for our country. I've seen many of these programs on youtube and wanted to add it to my collection.

WAS IN 3RD GRADE & STUDYING PRESIDENTS WHEN KENNEDY WAS ASSASINATED....... REMEMBER TEACHERS CRYING, SCHOOL CLOSING EARLY AND BEING OUT OF SCHOOL OR ABOUT 10 DAYS.(TOTAL)  AND EVERYONE TRANSFIXED IN FRONT OF THE TELEVISION..... THE KENNEDY FAMILY REMAINED A CONSTANT PRESENCE & FIXTURE FOR CHILDREN BORN IN MY ERA.

I HAVE WATCHED MANY  PERIODIC  DOCUMENTARY PROGRAMS ABOUT THAT TIME FRAME  AND DECIDED TO ORDER SEVERAL OF THE BEST DOCUMENTARIES FOR MY KEEPING..... I THINK THE WORLD WAS ENAMORED BY THEM & THE  KENNEDY FAMILY AND THE SUBSEQUENT TRADGEDIES & MISFORTUNES THAT FOLLOWED..

I choose this rating because the picture was clear. Watched the whole thing. Brought back memories of some of his speeches. Some of these speeches I have never seen before.
I would like to recommend this to someone who is a history nut.
This dvd is well worth the price.  It covers a lot of President Kennedy's time in the White House to the day he was buried.
this is a good summary of the years 1960-1963 but I found it too short and missing some events I think should have been added and that is why I gave only 4 stars, but in a whole it is well done
